Addressing reporters on Friday afternoon at St George Hotel in Irene Pretoria ANC spokesperson Zizi Kodwa said Zuma was invited in his capacity as the president of the ANC."The integrity commission has invited the president in his capacity as the president of the ANC to a meeting with the commission to discuss the state of the African National and the health of ANC " said Kodwa.This statement follows the Mail &amp; Guardian s report that Zuma will appear before the ANC s integrity commission. The date has apparently been set for 3 December.Zuma will reportedly be questioned on the ruling that he violated the Constitution in his handling of the Nkandla report and on the former public protector s State of Capture report which raised links to the controversial Gupta family.